#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
Integrates the REAL BASS core SDK (bundled BASS.java source +
libbass.so per ABI — see bass_native_libs.zip, extract separately)
with automatic fallback to MediaPlayer, plus the app-side wiring so
the karaoke lyric-sync clock reads from BASS once BASSMIDI is added.

IMPORTANT — two-part delivery for this round:
  1. This script writes all the Java/Gradle/README changes below.
  2. Separately extract bass_native_libs.zip into
     app/src/main/ (adds the real libbass.so per ABI) --
     run BOTH before rebuilding.

Current status after this: BASS core is fully wired with real,
compile-time-checked calls (no reflection for BASS itself anymore).
BASSMIDI -- the add-on that actually plays MIDI files and loads
SoundFonts -- is a SEPARATE download from un4seen and has not been
supplied yet, so the app still transparently falls back to
MediaPlayer for actual playback until that is added too. See
app/libs/README.md (added by this script) for exactly what is
still needed.

Usage (run from the repo root, e.g. ~/PureNeroflix in Termux):
    unzip -o ~/Download/bass_native_libs.zip -d app/src/main/
    python3 apply_bass_core_integration.py
"""
